      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Former Kiwi SNAP SHOT NZ (7) progressed strongly at her second outing for Brad Hewitt when she drifted back but surged home strongly for a 5.5m win at Wagga. She'll be hitting peak fitness now and has more upside than most of these. ELEGANT STRIDE (9) was a beaten favourite last start at this circuit and distance but still boxed on after leading to place. Draws wide but has the talent to measure up with her A-game and some luck. SEASIDE BOULEVARD (5) led and faded to fourth behind Snap Shot as a hot favourite last start but her other two starts this time in were strong so she could bounce back. BETTINE (3) came from the back row to find winning form here last start. A good draw could see her go on with it. WHERE BACK (2) worked when runner-up to BETTINE last start. She should enjoy better favours from this draw.",
